description:
Mentioned at length in the well-known Ten Commandments of Judaism and Christianity, the Sabbath is a key spoke in the wheel of the Seventh-day Adventist understanding and appreciation of the Bible. 

But what is it? Where did it come from? And why is it still important thousands of years after its inception at the beginning of the world? 

Does the Sabbath matter today? And should Christians keep the Sabbath? This introductory video seeks to introduce the theme and practice of Sabbath, and will hopefully encourage you and others that you share it with to go deeper into studying the Sabbath in scripture for yourselves. 

More in-depth explorations of the Sabbath in the Bible and how we practice it as Christians today are available at [https://www.adventist.org/the-sabbath/].

To follow our official social media accounts, just follow the links below:
